                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Balt<hi rend=\"sup\">o</hi></placeName>\n                                        <date>11th October 1852</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I owe you many apologies<lb/> for not having\n                                        sooner acknowledged your kind<lb/> favor of the\n                                                  <date>16th</date> ult<hi rend=\"sup\">o</hi> your\n                                        remark that I<lb/> might return the Book \"at my leisure\" I\n                                        took<lb/> advantage of since in truth I have been<lb/>\n                                        exceedingly occupied. The late holidays<lb/> I am in hopes\n                                        will have had the same<lb/> tendency with others that they\n                                        had with me,<lb/> viz to remind them to supply any\n                                        deficiency<lb/> of Prayer books required for the use of\n                                        their<lb/> families, and if you have not already<lb/> filled\n                                        up your subscription list, that<lb/> you may soon do so. We\n                                        have already<lb/> three sets, but my wife insists upon\n                                        having<lb/> another, which we wish bound in best style<lb/>\n                                        and lettered on the cover with \"<persName>Andrew J.\n                                                  Cohen</persName>\"s<lb/> name. I enclose you six\n                                        Dollars amot. of<lb/> your Bill and will feel obliged by\n                                        your procuring<lb/> and transmit me <persName>Dr.\n                                                  Raphaels</persName> work \"<add>רחמה</add>\" or<lb/>\n                                        devotional exercises for women.</p>\n                              <p>My wife, <persName>Andrew</persName> &amp;\n                                                  <persName>Frances</persName> desire to be<lb/>\n                                        kindly remembered, and believe me</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">Yours Truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">E. P. Cohen</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72m63/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
